              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 831,
            "end": 904,
            "text": "For Fe(III), hydrolysis and preference for anionic hard O‑donors dominate",
            "claim_type": "domain_reasoning",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 906,
            "end": 964,
            "text": "neutral donors like these are outcompeted by water and OH−",
            "claim_type": "domain_reasoning",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 966,
            "end": 1030,
            "text": "so conditional stability is negligible under typical aqueous pH.",
            "claim_type": "domain_reasoning",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 1033,
            "end": 1050,
            "text": "Important caveat:",
            "claim_type": "filler",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 1051,
            "end": 1104,
            "text": "SRD‑46 primarily curates aqueous formation constants.",
            "claim_type": "citation",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 1105,
            "end": 1282,
            "text": "Solvation/coordination in neat nonaqueous media (e.g., FeXn(MeCN)m in acetonitrile, solvated Fe(ClO4)2 in DMF/THF) are generally outside the aqueous stability‑constant framework",
            "claim_type": "domain_reasoning",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 1283,
            "end": 1312,
            "text": "and are not represented here.",
            "claim_type": "existence_absence",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 1313,
            "end": 1407,
            "text": "Thus, lack of aqueous β values does not preclude inner‑sphere solvation in those pure solvents",
            "claim_type": "domain_reasoning",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          },
          {
            "start": 1409,
            "end": 1495,
            "text": "it means SRD‑46 does not tabulate corresponding equilibrium constants for those media.",
            "claim_type": "existence_absence",
            "metadata": {
              "classifier_strategy_version": "react-v7-schema-salvage-markdown-anchor",
              "classifier_round": 0,
              "classifier_stage": "initial"
            }
          }
        ],
        "grounded_claims": []
      },
      {
        "paragraph_index": 6,
        "text": "Bottom line\n- SRD‑46 contains no aqueous stability constants for DMF–Fe(II/III), MeCN–Fe(II/III), THF–Fe(II/III), or EG–Fe(II/III). Given the database’s comprehensive coverage of Fe complexes that do form appreciably, the practical inference for water at ~25 °C and μ ≲ 0.1–1 M is that these neutral donors bind Fe(II/III) only very weakly (effectively negligible compared to aquo/hydrolyzed species). EG may chelate slightly more than the others when neutral, but remains minor unless deprotonated to alkoxide at high pH (then it is no longer “ethylene glycol” as a neutral ligand).",
